0:14:29.52,000 --> 0:14:32,000
if you're told by your work colleagues that you're looking tired and irritable,

295
0:14:33.342,000 --> 0:14:35,000
chances are you are sleep-deprived.

296
0:14:35.691,000 --> 0:14:37,000
Listen to them. Listen to yourself.

297
0:14:37.824,000 --> 0:14:38,000
What do you do?

298
0:14:39.291,000 --> 0:14:41,000
Well -- and this is slightly offensive --

299
0:14:41.348,000 --> 0:14:42,000
sleep for dummies.

300
0:14:42.529,000 --> 0:14:44,000
(Laughter)

301
0:14:44.673,000 --> 0:14:46,000
Make your bedroom a haven for sleep.

302
0:14:47.482,000 --> 0:14:5,000
The first critical thing is make it as dark as you possibly can,

303
0:14:51.01,000 --> 0:14:52,000
and also make it slightly cool.

304
0:14:52.875,000 --> 0:14:53,000
Very important.

305
0:14:54.051,000 --> 0:14:56,000
Actually, reduce your amount of light exposure

306
0:14:56.981,000 --> 0:14:58,000
at least half an hour before you go to bed.

307
0:14:59.354,000 --> 0:15:01,000
Light increases levels of alertness and will delay sleep.

308
0:15:02.131,000 --> 0:15:04,000
What's the last thing that most of us do before we go to bed?

309
0:15:05.018,000 --> 0:15:07,000
We stand in a massively lit bathroom,

310
0:15:07.411,000 --> 0:15:09,000
looking into the mirror cleaning our teeth.

311
0:15:09.53,000 --> 0:15:12,000
It's the worst thing we can possibly do before we go to sleep.

312
0:15:13.109,000 --> 0:15:15,000
Turn off those mobile phones. Turn off those computers.

313
0:15:15.836,000 --> 0:15:18,000
Turn off all of those things that are also going to excite the brain.

314
0:15:20.155,000 --> 0:15:22,000
Try not to drink caffeine too late in the day,

315
0:15:22.843,000 --> 0:15:24,000
ideally not after lunch.

316
0:15:25.715,000 --> 0:15:28,000
Now, we've set about reducing light exposure before you go to bed,

317
0:15:29.04,000 --> 0:15:3,000
but light exposure in the morning

318
0:15:30.996,000 --> 0:15:33,000
is very good at setting the biological clock to the light-dark cycle.

319
0:15:34.311,000 --> 0:15:35,000
So seek out morning light.

320
0:15:35.994,000 --> 0:15:37,000
Basically, listen to yourself.

321
0:15:38.474,000 --> 0:15:39,000
Wind down.

322
0:15:39.65,000 --> 0:15:4,000
Do those sorts of things

323
0:15:40.836,000 --> 0:15:42,000
that you know are going to ease you off

324
0:15:42.882,000 --> 0:15:44,000
into the honey-heavy dew of slumber.

325
0:15:46.195,000 --> 0:15:47,000
OK.

326
0:15:47.378,000 --> 0:15:49,000
That's some facts. What about some myths?

327
0:15:49.704,000 --> 0:15:5,000
Teenagers are lazy.

328
0:15:51.01,000 --> 0:15:52,000
No. Poor things.

329
0:15:52.898,000 --> 0:15:55,000
They have a biological predisposition to go to bed late and get up late,

